subSubSection.paragraph:
Selaginella nanuzae

is characterized by the upper surfaces of the leaves shiny (due to waxy deposits) and bumpy (Figs 
1
, 
2
), the median leaves long-aristate (Fig. 
1A, B, E, F
), the acroscopic margins of the lateral leaves (Fig. 
2B-D, E, G
) and both margins of the axillary and median leaves (Fig. 
1B-D, F-H
) broadly hyaline, as well as the apices of the lateral leaves acute (Fig. 
1A, E
; Fig. 
2A, B, E, G
).
